Package: wireguardrtc
Architecture: all
Depends: python3,
         python3-venv,
         wireguard-tools,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: WireGuard NAT hole-punching daemon via WebRTC signalling
 wireguardrtc maintains direct UDP tunnels between WireGuard peers behind
 cone NATs (full-cone, address-restricted, port-restricted) without
 requiring a relay server or a static public IP on either end.
 .
 Endpoint addresses are discovered via STUN and exchanged through a PeerJS
 signalling broker using the standard PeerJS OFFER wire format. Payloads are
 end-to-end encrypted using keys derived from the peers' WireGuard
 Curve25519 identities; the broker cannot read or forge endpoint updates.
 .
 After receiving a valid update the daemon punches the local NAT by
 injecting a raw UDP packet from the WireGuard listen port, updates the
 kernel endpoint with wg-set(8), and triggers a fresh handshake.
 .
 Supported peer modes: active (proactive signalling), passive (accept
 incoming only), dns-roam (track a dynamic DNS hostname), ignore.
